<p>
  GOV.UK Boostrap combines the <a href="http://govuk-elements.herokuapp.com/">GOV.UK Element</a>
  and <a href="http://getbootstrap.com/">Bootstrap</a> style frameworks, and is published as an NPM <a href="https://www.npmjs.com/package/govuk_bootstrap">package</a>.
</p>
<h2>Usage</h2>
<p>
  Include the dependency in the <code>package.json</code> file of your front end application. No further dependencies are required.
</p>
<p>
  <code>
    {
      "govuk_bootstrap": "^0.0.5"
    }
  </code>
</p>
<p>
  Once the module is installed, serve the <code>dist/assets</code> directory which contains the compiled css stylesheet and the image files.
  Alternatively, the source files are available in the <code>dist/sass</code> directory for manual compilation and/or extension.
</p>
